{"id": "12d5d501-22f1-485b-9923-15e11a0cfb69", "value": "Aquatic invertebrate animals whose outer covering is a shell, often 'farmed' to be eaten. Includes molluscs and crustaceans."}

{"id": "46a320ea-4460-4faa-a012-967d9dcc8ebb", "value": "The hard material, consisting mainly of calcium compounds, which makes up the skeleton of vertebrates. Used for ornaments or ground for use in the manufacture of bone china."}

Most examples date from the Middle Ages, obsolete from the 17th century."}

{"id": "178be7eb-30b4-4def-a647-9fa07068892d", "value": "Fibres of wood reduced chemically or mechanically to pulp for use in the manufacture of paper."}

{"id": "0617c753-dc38-47ba-aa7e-07bb44c5de83", "value": "Frozen water. Prior to the invention of the refrigerator, ice was used to preserve food."}

{"id": "de619c4c-7520-4fc9-8917-d653b2b69799", "value": "Machinery and equipment used in the manufacture of aircraft."}
{"id": "edaa9848-1943-4b5f-883a-b60320861721", "value": "Bed coverings, usually of woollen or similar natural or artificial fabrics."}
